sentences.english: There are vast fields of sugarcane in Queensland, Australia.

sentences.english: The Queensland National Trust has named it a state icon of Queensland.
sentences.chinese: 昆士兰国民托管组织命名它为昆士兰州的象征。

sentences.english: Its bones were found on a farm in north-eastern Australia's Queensland state.
sentences.chinese: 在东北部澳大利亚昆士兰州国营农场发现它的骨骼。

sentences.english: A herd of sheep grazes in a pasture in Queensland.
sentences.chinese: 昆士兰州，一群绵羊在牧场上吃草。

sentences.english: In western Queensland, army marksmen have been called in to shoot feral cats.
sentences.chinese: 在昆士兰州西部，已经召集军队神枪手射杀野猫。

sentences.english: The specimen will be taken to the Riversleigh Fossil Centre, a World Heritage site in Queensland.
sentences.chinese: 该样本将被送往昆士兰州的世界遗产化石中心。

sentences.english: He was selected for the gig by officials from the tour ism department of Queen sland state.
sentences.chinese: 他是被澳大利亚昆士兰州旅游主管部门的官员选中的。

sentences.english: I must reside in the State of Queensland during the period of my provisional visa.
